RDP SHORTPATH FOR AVD
Uses UDP-based transport between client & session host
Improves reliability & latency

DEFAULT BEHAVIOR
Starts with TCP reverse connect
Attempts UDP connection
Falls back to TCP if UDP fails

UDP BENEFITS
Better latency
Better reliability

TCP BENEFITS
Better compatibility
High connection success rate

RDP SHORTPATH TYPES

1.MANAGED NETWORK
Uses private connection:
ExpressRoute
Site-to-Site VPN
Direct UDP connection

METHODS
1.Enable UDP listener + inbound port
2.Use STUN protocol (no inbound port required)

2.PUBLIC NETWORK
Uses public internet
Types:
a) Direct UDP using STUN
b) Relayed UDP using TURN

IMPORTANT
Managed network requires UDP listener
Default UDP Port = 3390
Can change to unused port

RDP SHORTPATH CONFIGURATION
Host Pool → Networking → RDP Shortpath
